Following, we describe how we adopt pairwise alignment methods to generate similarity scores in temporal networks that are needed to calculate an initial alignment. For that purpose, we consider adopting IsoRank. We note that our choice of such method has no impact on our method. Recall that IsoRank perform pairwise network alignment. Thus, our modifications of IsoRank are meant to adopt it to temporal networks. First, we calculate the homology score between all pairs of nodes (u,v) where u∈V1 and v∈V2 as the similarity score of their sequences using BLAST [35]. We denote the homology score between u and v as H[u,v]. Next, we calculate the topological similarity matrix at the ith time point, denoted as Ai, as follows. First, we initialize Ai to be the zero matrix. Next, for u,w∈V1 and v,z∈V2 we let \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
