The first condition above ensures that node ui is swapped with a gap node and the second ensures the dynamic programming iterates over all size r−1 swap sets for all aligned nodes of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\mathcal {G}^{2}$\end{document}G2. The third condition ensures that the aligned node ui has not already been swapped in the r−1 sized swap set. The final condition is the dual of the previous one, as it ensures that the gap node vi has not already been swapped in the r−1 sized swap set. When these conditions hold, the two nodes ui and vi can be swapped and included into the existing set of r−1 swaps without conflicting with any of the existing swaps.

